\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Nuclear fusion represents the next frontier in energy generation, promising a virtually limitless and clean energy source by mimicking the processes that power the sun. Unlike nuclear fission, which splits atoms, fusion involves combining atomic nuclei to release energy. Recent advances in magnetic confinement, inertial confinement, and plasma physics are bringing fusion closer to practical application. However, significant engineering challenges remain before fusion can be a viable energy source, including achieving and maintaining the extreme conditions necessary for fusion to occur.}